What is derived
---------------
The three bricks arrive as git submodules under external/ and carry
their own NOTICE files (CTLL/CTRE lineage, the Lark grammar language
by Erez Shinan and the lark-parser project, the WHATWG entity data,
the ECMA-262 and W3C CSS semantics). This repository began as a clone
of compile-time-css - the chain runs compile-time-xml ->
compile-time-html -> compile-time-css -> here - and keeps that git
history. The page-assembly glue (type -> text -> type re-entry), the
runtime DOM, the layout engine, the script bindings and the SDL3
shell are original to this repository.

Attribution for the parser architecture and the CTLL engine belongs to
Hana Dusikova; this file preserves it as required by Section 4(c) of
the Apache License 2.0.

The embedded 8x8 bitmap font (include/ctbrowser/font8x8.hpp) is
PUBLIC DOMAIN: font8x8 by Daniel Hepper <daniel@hepper.net>
(https://github.com/dhepper/font8x8), based on public-domain work by
Marcel Sondaar / International Business Machines.

The PNG writer (include/ctbrowser/stb_image_write.h) is stb_image_write
v1.16, and the image loader (include/ctbrowser/stb_image.h, used to decode
glTF baseColor textures at runtime) is stb_image v2.30, both by Sean
Barrett and contributors (https://github.com/nothings/stb), used under
their PUBLIC DOMAIN (Unlicense) option.

The example assets (examples/assets/) are generated deterministically
by tools/gen-assets.py in this repository and carry no third-party
content, with one exception: the font
examples/assets/fonts/PressStart2P-Regular.ttf is "Press Start 2P" by
CodeMan38 (Cody Boisclair), used and redistributed under the SIL Open
Font License, Version 1.1 (the license text is alongside the font at
examples/assets/fonts/OFL.txt).

The Space Invaders 3D models (examples/assets/models/*.glb: Alien_1/2/3,
Player_1, MotherShip) are from John Pitchers' Space-Invaders
(https://github.com/johnpitchers/Space-Invaders), used under CC0.

Simple DirectMedia Layer (SDL3, https://libsdl.org) and its optional
satellite libraries SDL3_image, SDL3_mixer and SDL3_ttf are used as
external dependencies and are NOT bundled; all are distributed under
the zlib license.

The compile-time file API (include/ctbrowser/embed.hpp) follows the
__builtin_std_embed call protocol of phd::embed from the "embed"
project by Bjorkus "ThePhD" Dorkus (https://github.com/ThePhD/embed),
dedicated to the public domain under CC0.
